name:                array
stack:               ( define: u -- ) ( run: u1 -- u2 )
return stack:        ( -- )
string stack:        ( -- )
contexts:            stateless
category:            defining word
input stream:        space delimited string

decription:          parse a space delimited string from input stream and create an
                     array instance by that name. allocate u cells to the array.
                     When executing the defined array, an array index on stack is
                     replaced against the corresponding item address.
                     Items in newly defined arrays are ininitialised.
